==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Four-way stop
<hw>Four"-way` stop</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An
intersection of two roads having stop signs at all four entry points.
The usual rule for such intersections requires that those entering the
intersection yield the right of way to vehicles entering before
them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 591 --></p>

